homeAbout.Paragraphs:
Smart ESA is an accelerator program offered by ESA Business School in Lebanon that helps transform creative individuals into successful entrepreneurs. The program equips startups with a comprehensive management toolkit to promote sustainable success and empower entrepreneurs to take their businesses to the next level.
Since its founding in 2017, Smart ESA has become the most successful accelerator program in Lebanon, graduating more than 40 startups and 50 projects across 10 programs. The program's impressive track record is reflected in the success of its portfolio startups, which have achieved remarkable results in prestigious competitions across the MENA region, including GITEX, Amadeus Travel Tech Challenge, Arab Startup Competition at Harvard Business School, and the MIT Enterprise Forum Pan Arab competition.
Smart ESA's methodology is anchored in practical entrepreneurship expertise, providing startups with the knowledge, skills, and resources necessary to thrive in today's competitive business landscape. By fostering a culture of innovation, creativity, and collaboration, Smart ESA is helping to shape the future of entrepreneurship in Lebanon and beyond.

internationaProgramHome.title: INTERNATIONAL PROGRAMS
internationaProgramHome.Paragraphs:
Providing entrepreneurs with an unsurpassed methodology, offering workshops, one-on-one mentoring, extensive access to high-profile and international experts
For entrepreneurs with just an idea at the beginning of their journey, looking forward to create a business and transform their idea into a potential and successful business;  our Create Program is the right one for you !
For start-ups with a Minimum Viable Product (MVP) and early traction, our Boost Program is aiming to grow your company and improve your sales.

OURCOMMUNITYHome.title: OURCOMMUNITY
OURCOMMUNITYHome.Paragraphs:
Smart ESA has an established reputation in the startup ecosystem, having worked with more than 90 emerging companies and partnered with 70 experienced coaches.
Additionally, they have developed strategic alliances with leading businesses in France, Lebanon, the United States, and beyond, which highlights their dedication to fostering entrepreneurship and innovation on a global scale.

ContactHome.title: Contact Home
ContactHome.Paragraphs:
Connecting with us is just a click away! Whether you have a question, comment, or just want to say hello, we're always here to listen.
Don't hesitate to reach out and start a conversation - we can't wait to hear from you!

AboutUsHome.title: About Us
AboutUsHome.Paragraphs:
Smart ESA is the ESA Business School Accelerator, working to transform creators into entrepreneurs by providing startups with a management toolbox for sustainable success. Smart ESA welcomes all entrepreneurs across Lebanon. +40 startups and +50 projects have graduated from the +10 programs. Founded in 2017, Smart ESA is recognized as the most successful accelerator program in Lebanon. It was elected best Accelerator in Lebanon in 2018 and won the Social Economic Awards in 2017.
The program follows a unique methodology with each of its projects that focuses on three main pillars: vision, customer, and execution. Smart ESA places a heavy weight on 'getting it done' and achieving milestones in a timely, top-quality manner.
The startups in the portfolio are recognized as some of the most successful from Lebanon, and many have won some of the most prestigious competitions in the MENA region such as GITEX, Amadeus Travel Tech Challenge, Arab Startup Competition at Harvard Business School, and the MIT Enterprise Forum Pan Arab competition. Smart ESA's methodology is anchored in practical entrepreneurship expertise.

SamartTalkHome.title: Smart Talk
SamartTalkHome.Paragraphs:
Welcome to SmartTalk, the first-ever web TV dedicated to entrepreneurship in Lebanon and the Arab world. Our platform provides a unique opportunity to connect with industry leaders,entrepreneurs, investors, and ecosystem experts, and gain valuable insights on building successful businesses that stand the test of time.
 Our engaging and informative content is designed to equip aspiring and established entrepreneurs with the tools and knowledge they need to achieve their goals.
Join us as we explore the latest trends, best practices, and success stories in the world of entrepreneurship, and embark on a journey towards building a thriving and sustainable business.

EventsHome.title: Events
EventsHome.Paragraphs:
Relive the magic of our past events! From stunning performances to engaging talks, our events have left a lasting impact on everyone who attended. Our carefully curated events are designed to bring people together and create unforgettable memories.
Now, you can relive those special moments and memories by browsing through our collection of past events. From photos and videos to recaps and highlights, our archive offers a glimpse into the amazing experiences we've created. So come take a journey through time and see for yourself what makes our events so special!

coursesCard.OBJECTIVE: Win a 6 Months Incubation Program at Station F – Paris
coursesCard.AboutALL:
ESA Business school, in partnership with Smart ESA and HEC Alumni in Lebanon, have come together to organize the third edition of “ESA - HEC Entrepreneur Award”, as part of their  efforts to create a suitable environment for the emergence of Lebanese entrepreneurs.

The competition is supported by Air France, French Embassy in Lebanon, La French Tech Beyrouth and Chamber of Commerce, Industry and Agriculture in Beirut and Mount Lebanon.

This competition, open for all the Lebanese, both in the country and abroad, aims to support  Lebanese entrepreneurs as they create innovative projects to foster the vast potential that Lebanon has to offer.

The winner(s) of the Award will receive a six month-incubation in France, at the world's biggest startup campus, Station F. The winner(s) will also benefit from exceptional visibility in the media, via L’Orient-Le Jour.

And all finalists will benefit from a support program provided by the Smart ESA incubator, scholarships to the Masters in Entrepreneurship and Innovation at ESA (a program developed in partnership with HEC Paris and Smart ESA) and from generous Air France offers.

Applications must be submitted before 31 May 2023.

The competition is only open for enterprises in their design phase, or for those created less than 24 months ago, and which are presently undertaking the development of a product and have a turnover of less than $500K.

A)                   Applications - Eligibility 

Candidates should prove that:
•                      The project came in response to a problem or clear necessity
•                      The project brings clear innovation to existing processes/products
•                      The project is viable and profitable in the long term
•                      The project has international potential

B)                   Participation guidelines

Applications should be only presented online, and all the required information should be submitted via the form at the bottom of this page.

C)                   Confidentiality 

All the information shared during the process of entering the competition remains the property of the project owner. The partners vow to keep it confidential and to protect the intellectual property of the candidates

blogs.title: Prix Entrepreneur ESA - HEC Paris 2021
blogs.desc:
Congratulations to the two winning startups of the competition:
In first place, Synapse, a clinical communications platform linking health and social care providers. In second place, Podeo, a podcasting platform dedicated to managing, producing and distributing audio podcasts in the Arab world.
Special thank you to the competition’s supporters, sponsors and all the finalists.
blogs.paragraphs:
Another successful edition of the Prix Entrepreneur ESA - HEC Paris competition, an initiative by the ESA Business School and HEC Paris.

The winning startups receive an exceptional prize to be sent over to the HEC Incubateur in Station F, Paris - all expenses paid, for six months, with free travel tickets by Air France.

blogs.title: Ed'Innov Launch
blogs.desc:
Porté par l’Ambassade de France au Liban et l’ESA, le projet Ed’Innov est un groupement qui rassemble les acteurs de l’éducation et de l’innovation Ed-tech, libanais et français afin de faire émerger des solutions innovantes au service et au bénéfice de la qualité de l’enseignement au Liban, en particulier francophone.
Responsables institutionnels, enseignants, étudiants, parents d’élèves, chercheurs, experts de l’éducation francophone, éditeurs et entrepreneurs du numérique éducatif sont ainsi appelés à travailler ensemble pour développer l’accès pour tous aux solutions innovantes et contribuer au développement du secteur économique du numérique éducatif au Liban.
Devant une centaine de participants en présentiel et en ligne, Mme Grillo a rappelé l’engagement de la France en faveur de l’éducation au Liban. Elle a appelé de ses vœux une mobilisation commune en faveur d’une dynamique d’avenir pour préserver, grâce à l’innovation, l’excellence de l’éducation francophone au Liban, tout en soulignant l’exemplarité d’un système éducatif qui tire sa force de son pluralisme, de sa diversité et de sa capacité à jouer un rôle fondamental pour la cohésion du pays.
M. Maxence Duault, Directeur de l’ESA Business School, a souligné à son tour le fort potentiel de l’incubateur Smart Esa, qui a jusqu’à présent accompagné une centaine de startups libanaises et s’ouvre de plus en plus au secteur de l’éducation. Les enjeux et les défis sont immenses, tant sur les plans technologique qu’éducatif : Ed’Innov fonctionnera comme un centre de « recherche et développement » collectif, au service de l’éducation au Liban.
Les prochains rendez-vous :
En septembre prochain, Ed’Innov démarrera un programme d’accélération de quatre mois, afin d’accompagner les startups libanaises du numérique éducatif au sein de Smart ESA. Un hackathon sera organisé, en novembre, autour de « l’innovation frugale », en réponse aux besoins de solutions éducatives accessibles et peu coûteuses. Enfin une conférence internationale portant sur l’innovation dans le secteur éducatif à Beyrouth viendra clore l’année 2021.

blogs.title: Global Innovation & Enterprise
blogs.desc:
IE-Club, in partnership with Smart ESA, hosted the Global Innovation and Enterprise pitching event in 2021, with a special focus on Lebanese startups. The event provided a unique platform for ten established startups founded in Lebanon to pitch their ideas to major European corporates and investors.

This offered an excellent opportunity for the Lebanese startups to gain exposure to global investors and establish potential business partnerships with European corporates. The event aimed to facilitate collaboration between international investors and the Lebanese startup ecosystem and promote the growth of innovative startups in the country.
blogs.paragraphs:
With a special focus on Lebanese startups in 2021, IE-Club hosted another round of its Global Innovation and Enterprise pitching event in collaboration with Smart ESA.

IE-Club and its partners offered a unique opportunity for 10 established, Lebanese-founded startups to pitch to major European corporates and investors.

blogs.title: Demo Day 2020
blogs.desc:
Smart ESA's program is the result of a collaboration between ESA Business School, the French Embassy in Lebanon, and the Central Bank of Lebanon.
 By leveraging the network and expertise of its founding members, Smart ESA provides a unique journey for its startup batches, focusing on developing three pillars: Great Vision, Customers first-approach, and Impactful Execution.
Through this approach, Smart ESA aims to foster entrepreneurial success and drive positive impact in Lebanon and beyond.
blogs.paragraphs:
Smart ESA, a program for outstanding Lebanese entrepreneurs, recently concluded its ninth consecutive program, Boost 2020, in partnership with MAGNiTT and Air France.

 The Demo Day event saw seven Smart ESA startups presenting their projects to hundreds of viewers, including investors, industry experts, entrepreneurs, and members of the press.

blogs.title: ESA Coding Lab
blogs.desc:
We are delighted to announce the launch of the ESA Coding Lab, in collaboration with our partners, Agence Française de Développement and ITESCIA. The ESA Coding Lab is a comprehensive full-stack development training program that spans over four months and awards a dual certificate from France and Lebanon upon completion.

 This program aims to provide students with the necessary skills and knowledge to become proficient full-stack developers, enabling them to contribute to the growth of the tech industry in Lebanon and beyond.
The ESA Coding Lab is based in the French Institute of Nabatiyeh with a second location to be announced during 2021.
blogs.paragraphs:
We proudly announce the launch of the ESA Coding Lab with the great help of our partners, Agence Française de Développement and ITESCIA.

The ESA Coding Lab is a 4-month full-stack development training program that offers a dual certificate from France and Lebanon.

blogs.title: Prix ESA-HEC Paris 2020
blogs.desc:
catching each of the jury member’s eyes, Myceleum (founded by Bassem Makarem and Ghassan Achi), a startup that greatly simplifies the process of creating and updating projects for tech companies and developers, will also be heading to Station F, Paris for a 3-month incubation program.
The Prix ESA-HEC Paris is a yearly competition in partnership with HEC Paris, ESA Business School and Smart ESA where the best startups in Lebanon pitch to international jury members to be granted the opportunity to head over to Station F, Paris for 6 months.
blogs.paragraphs:
Congratulations to startups DIM and Myceleum on winning 1st and 2nd place in the first edition of the Prix ESA-HEC Paris prize.

DIM, a ConTech startup that offers an on-site management optimization tool founded by Michella Abou Jawdeh, received a cash prize of $10,000 and a 3-month incubation at Station F, Paris.

blogs.title: Hackathon La Mode en 2050
blogs.desc:
Lebanon's first-ever fashion-inspired Hackathon, 'Hackathon: La Mode en 2050', brought together five teams comprising members from different universities to compete in an exciting challenge.
The event was made possible thanks to the support of the Ambassade de France à Beyrouth and the Agence Universitaire de la Francophonie (AUF), and the participation of several universities.
The teams showcased their innovative ideas and solutions for the future of fashion, demonstrating their creativity, expertise, and passion for the industry. We extend our special thanks to all involved for their contribution to the success of this event.
blogs.paragraphs:
The participants of the 'Hackathon: La Mode en 2050'. Five teams, each member from a different university, went head-to-head to compete in Lebanon's first ever fashion-inspired Hackathon.

Special thank you to Ambassade de France à Beyrouth & Agence Universitaire de la Francophonie (AUF) for making this event possible, and all participating universities.

blogs.title: Hack The City
blogs.desc:
Hack The City workshop was a 3 days event sponsored by the Municipality of Beirut . The event was won by the Jarak Startup,  an application helping communities connect to each others.
The hackathon is a 72-hour event during which participants will work in teams to find solutions to make the city better! During the hackathon, the teams will undergo extensive training and mentorship with experts in Business, Urbanism, Design, IT and Pitching to enable them to pitch their solution to two selection juries (local and international).

If you are interested in becoming a coach, contact us at 01 373 373
